Date: Wed, 14 Jul 1999 09:53:13 -0300
From: "Dr. Oscar P. Larghi" <oplarghi@drwebsa.com.ar>

I'd agree with Arthur that FAT is an excellent test but is not infallible.
The experience in dozens of Latin American and Southeastern Asia labs taught
me that several factors influence its sensitivity. Among them I'd mention:
a) Waiting for the development of symptoms in the biting animal
b) Preservation of brain samples
c) Proper sampling of the nervous tissue (Ammon's horn, cerebral cortex and
cerebellum)
d) Proper adjustment of conjugate working dilution to the microscope in use
(Larghi et all. Rev Inst Med Trop (S. Paolo) 28: 2-5, 1986).
---
Oscar Larghi
Buenos Aires
Argentina
<oplarghi@drwebsa.com.ar>
